===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} ''[[#Middle English|certain, certein]]'' from {{etyl|fro}} ''[[#Old French|certain]]'' from [[w:Late Latin|Vulgar Latin]] unattested form *{{term||certānus}}, extended form of {{etyl|la}} {{term|certus||fixed, resolved, certain}}, of the same origin as {{term|cretus}}, pp. of {{term|cernere||to separate, perceive, decide}}. Displaced native {{enm}} ''[[wis#Middle English|wis, iwis]]'' "certain, sure" (from {{ang}} ''[[gewiss#Old English|ġewis, ġewiss]]'' "certain, sure"), and non-native {{enm}} ''[[sertane#Middle English|sertane]]'' "some, certain" (from {{enm}} ''[[#Middle English|certain]]'').

